title: Winfield hosts home cross country meet
text:
Winfield hosts home cross country meet Oct 02, 2015 Photo by: Andy Krutsinger Gavin Bencze runs for Winfield-Mt. Union in the home meet on Thursday. Bencze went on to finish second overall. 
BY ANDY KRUTSINGER 
Mt. Pleasant News 
WINFIELD — The WACO and Winfield-Mt. Union cross country teams competed in the annual Winfield meet on Thursday evening. 
The Wolves finished third in the boys’ race and fifth in the girls’ race, while the Warriors finished 11th in the boys race and didn’t have enough girls competing to qualify. 
Gavin Bencze, Johnathon Quinn and Drake Mehaffey gave the Wolves three top 10 finishes in the boys’ race. Benzce finished in second place, in 16:55; Quinn was fourth, in 17:31.06; and Mehaffey was 10th, in 18:16.72. 
Other finishers for the W-MU boys were Kohlton Heinzel (32nd, 19:29.03), Nick Davis (51st, 20:47.25), Kane Harris (61st, 21:52.22) and Ross Vantiger (64th, 23:28.78.) 
The WACO boys were led by John Skriver, who ran a 44th-place 20:23.81. Joe Edeker finished 58th, in 21:18.00; Roman Kiefer was 66th, in 23:39.88; Trevor Patagas was 67th, in 24:47.59; and Zachariah Parsons finished the race in a 71st place 35:07. 
In the girls’ race, it was Cecelia Hemsworth who led the way for W-MU with a 10th-place 22:31.72. Whitney Vantiger and Isabella Mertens finished 23rd and 24th, in 24:21.47 and 24:25.97 respectively. Kimberlee Warnstaff finished 33rd, in 26:08.66 and Fionna Sparrow was 39th, in 26:51.44. 
Cheynne Sedlacek led the WACO girls, finishing in 19th place with the time of 23:05.72. Michaela Shaffer ran in 36th place in 26:29.22 and Emily Thomas came in 45th place with a time of 29:20.84.
